<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9605> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9605" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 422" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9114> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9114" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 755, footnote 465" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8395> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8395" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 64, Promagistrates, and note 7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7848> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7848" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 56. Aed. Cur. 58. In MRR 2.195, on Scaurus and P. Plautius Hypsaeus (23), refer for their coinage to Crawford, RRC 1.446, no. 422.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5195> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5195" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Sardinia (Ascon. 18 C), probably Proconsul (CIL 12.2. 8 11). Prosecuted for extortion immediately after his return in 54, but acquitted (Cic. Scaur., passim; QF 2.15.3; 3.1.11; Alt. 4.16.6, cf. 15.9; Val. Max. 8.1.10; Ascon. 18-28 C). See 54, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5123> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5123" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Presided at the trial of Sestius (Cic. Sest. 101, and 116; Ascon. 16 C; perhaps named in CIL 12.2. 811). See 55, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The full list of the college of Pontifices, including the Flamen Martialis and the Flamen Quirinalis (no Flamen Dialis had been inaugurated since the death of Merula in 87) and the Pontifices Minores, as it was composed on September 29, 57, can be reconstructed from Cic. Har. Resp. 12:" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5043> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5043" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Grueber, CRRBM 1.483f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 (1942) 258f. Gave aedilician games of special magnificence (Cic. Off. 2.57; Sest. 116, and Schol. Bob. 135 Stangl; Val. Max. 2.4.6-7; Ascon. 18C; Plin. NH 8.64 and 96; 9.11; 34.36; 35.127; 36.50, 113-115, and 189; Ammian. Marc. 22.15.24; Solin. 32.31; 34.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4988> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4988" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The successors to P. Mucius Scaevola, Sex. Quinctilius Varus, Mam. Aemilius Lepidus, D. Iunius Silanus and Q. Latatius Catulus \n     were C. Fannius, M. Aemilius Lepidus, P. Cornelius Lentulus SPinther, M. Aemilius Scaurus, M. Licinius Crassus Dives, M. Licinius Crassus and C. Scribonius Curio. These lists of the Pontifices who died between the death of Metellus Pius in 64 or 63 (see 63, Pontifices) and that of Catulus (before May, 60, Cic. Att. 1.20.3; Dio 37.46.3-4), and of their successors, are based on the order of the lists of priests in Macrob. Sat. 3.13.11 (before 6913.C.) and in Cicero (Har. Resp. 12; Dom. 118; in 57 B.C.), and assume that in both cases they are named in the order of their inauguration into the college. The lower limit is drawn on the assumption that the two plebeians, Crassus, whether he be the Consul of 70 or his son, and Curio, are probably the successors of the two plebeians Silanus and Catulus. As the earlier list is not complete there is room for an additional name in the list of successors. On the whole question, see L. R. Taylor, AJPh 63 (1942) 384-412, esp. 388ff., and 411f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4944> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4944" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 63, and 62, Promagistrates. L. Marcius Philippus (see below) probably succeeded him in 61." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4907> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4907" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Remained in charge in Syria when Pompey returned to Asia Minor (see 63, and below, 62, Promagistrates, on Pompey). Began an invasion of Nabatean Arabia, but desisted in return for a payment of 300 talents (Joseph. AJ 14.80-81; BJ 1.159). See 66, Quaestors; and 65-63, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4864> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4864" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Pompey in Syria and Palestine (see 66, Quaestors; 65-64, Promagistrates), who left him in command there proquaestore propraetore (IGRP 3.1102-ILS 875) with two legions when he returned to Pontus (Joseph. AJ 14.79; BJ 1.157; Hegesipp. 1.18; App. Syr. 51; BC 5.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4827> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4827" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 66, Quaestors; and 65, Promagistrates. In Syria he became involved in the rivalries of the Jewish princes, and is charged with accepting bribes (Joseph. AJ 14.29-33 and 37; BJ 1.123-130; App. Syr. 51)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4791> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4791" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 66, Quaestors. In 65, or in 64 at the latest, he was active in Pompey's service in Syria. See 64, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9668> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9668" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
